name: Note for csv/excel sheets nodes
info:
The Procedure why it worked:
1. Output and save the excel data into computer with "excel sheets" node
2. Use "file in" node to get the file from computer and retained the file inside the "file in" node.
3. When "http request" gonna store the file, it will take the file from "file in" node, and save to the computer.
4. The computer's previous saved file by "excel sheets" have been replaced by the file that saving by "http request".

name: Note for html nodes
info:
-If the "html nodes" are in the same page, its actually connecting them together at last.

-If you named the methods with the same name in different "html node", and if you call the method (e.g. checkExist()) in one of the "html node", the other same named method in the other "html node" will also been triggered.

-If you are having multiple "html nodes" in the same page, the output will be sent via the last "html node", the "html node" before the last "html node" will not sending anything, it will only send via the last "html node".
